Text.Value: Murdered? ... Gods. He didn't deserve to die.
You wouldn't either, if you knew him like I did.
You've not quite got the patter nailed yet, Carmen.
Leave.
Welcome back to Carm's Garms, we've got clothes for your... arms? Um. What do you need?
So you didn't get on with your brother?
Perhaps leave the taglines to the experts, hm? You haven't quite nailed that patter.
So you don't get on with your brother?
That patter was atrocious. Garms and arms? Really?
But if it's genuine quality, and genuine taste, you're after - Carm's Garms has you covered.
Let's take a look at your wares.
I already told you - if patter's your main interest, go see my brother. My focus is good clothing for a good price.
If it's empty patter you want, get your clothes from my brother, Figaro.
Well, allow me to return the favour. He's a pig and a bastard.
I... see you're wearing some of my brother's handiwork. It suits your colouring. If you're interested in something to complement the look, welcome to Carm's Garms!

EditorData.NodeContext: a bit sad, her usual distaste for her brother's handiwork gone (brother is dead), tries to rally herself with more cheer at the end

Text.Value: Ahoy, stranger, thanks for stopping by Carm's Garms! I'm Carm - well, Carmen, hah. What can I do you for?

EditorData.NodeContext: she's nervous, a bit stammery, too quick to force a laugh

Text.Value: A killer? That's... gods. I've no love for my brother but that's extreme. He doesn't deserve that.
Thought me working on my own stuff was 'disrespectful'. But maybe he was just trying to keep me close after Dad... Who knows.
I'm afraid your brother's been murdered.
Maybe you should keep your nose out of where it doesn't bloody belong. Now, you want clothes or not?
Sounds good, get you something a bit... fresher than your current outfit.
He was... difficult. Always thought I should come work for him in Dad's old shop.
Cheers for that. If you... If you need clothes, you know where I am.

EditorData.NodeContext: If Carmen knows that her brother died, she will be a bit more absent-minded.

Text.Value: Glad to hear the snootiness doesn't run in the family. Now, while I'd happily stand hear and shite talk my brother all day - I've clothes to sell.
Yes... Well. I suppose he'd have wanted someone to clothe you lot.

EditorData.NodeContext: If Carmen knows that her brother died, she will be a bit more absent-minded.

Text.Value: Carmen? I think I met your brother, Figaro. He didn't speak highly of you.
Your brother is in danger. I found his name on a serial killer's list.
Since Dad died he thinks he's cock of the bloody walk. That I should give up my shop and work for 'family business'. For him. Dick.
You're a lot less snooty than that other clothes seller, Figaro.
Patter still needs a bit of work. Maybe less rhyming.
Remember - Carm's Garms, here for all your fashion needs!
Maybe Figaro wanted his sister close. You just lost your dad, after all.
Thanks for warning me. But it's him that needs warning. And he never listens to me.
I... see you're wearing some of my brother's handiwork. If... If you're interested in something with a bit more life to it, welcome to Carm's Garms!

Synopsis: Default dialogue with Carmen Pennygood, owner of a cosmetics shop in Wyrm's Crossing near Wyrm's Rock. Sister of Figaro "Facemaker" Pennygood, owner of a rival cosmetics shop in Baldur's Gate. They have a strained relationship.
